17. Story Interoperability

Because people inhabit different story systems, conflict often occurs at the runtime level rather than the factual level.

Two agents may agree on observations but disagree on:

* what counts as good,
* what role each person occupies,
* what caused the event,
* what must happen next,
* which ending is desirable.

Communication fails when information is sent without translating between narrative schemas.

A narrative translator would map:

T: N_A \rightarrow N_B

while preserving core meaning.

def translate_between_worldviews(message, source_story, target_story):
    invariant = extract_semantic_invariant(message, source_story)
    return render_in_story(invariant, target_story)

This unlocks a deeper form of communication:

Do not merely translate the words. Translate the role the words perform inside the world.

