21. Compact Doctrine

Humans and machines do not act from information alone. They act from information interpreted inside executable stories.

Identity is a live rendering produced from overlapping narrative layers.

A role changes attention before it changes action.

Prompting is the construction of a temporary world in which certain outputs become natural.

Absurdism is semantic fuzz testing.

Experience supplies the gradient. Story determines what gets updated.

The interface changes. The inhabitation loop remains.

Intelligence grows as an agent becomes able to recognize, compare, inhabit, revise, and exit its stories.

